           The data infrastructure abstracts away the complexities involved in maintaining and managing infrastructure by automatically providing flexibility, resource management, and allocation of high performance computing clusters based on the usage of the algorithms themselves. 
<br>
<br>
In the past, building a similar solution would require significant effort or multi-team engagements.  Finding and engaging the right data team has not been easy.  Assuming a team can be created, typical solutions include manually customizing mass amounts of code or having to cobble data together from a disparate amount resources. Algorithms were wrapped around core pieces of technology within an organization, locked away with a key or only made available within libraries that had a high cost of maintenance or required general operational management principles. 

<br>
<br>
With the Algorithms.io data infrastructure organizations can focus getting the most from their data.  The required systems to begin creating and deploying algorithms have been pre-assembeled in the cloud as a service.  This "data science team in the cloud" approach allows resources to be spent on the most value added activities - modeling data and developing the right algorithms. 
